{
  "texts": [
    "Further immunohistochemical stains for β-catenin (nuclear), cyclin D1, α-1-antichymotrypsin were positive.",
    "An 85-year-old woman presented with an ulcerated 3.5 cm nodule on the left temporal region.",
    "Following dermatological examination, the lesion was excised.",
    "On histology, hematoxylin&eosin stain demonstrated, throughout the dermis, multiple islands of small palisading cells with scant cytoplasm and uniform hyperchromatic nuclei intermixed with scattered aggregates of polygonal cells with atypical large nuclei, mitosis, and abundant eosinophilic cytoplasm.",
    "In addition, perineural invasion was seen."
  ]
}